<item>
            <title>[AMQ-6345] [MQTT] ping response without CONNECT</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-6345</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I am currently investigating the behavior of several MQTT brokers and noticed that the ActiveMQ broker responds to PINGREQ packets with PINGRESP packets even if no CONNECT packet has been sent before. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would be a violation of MQTT-3.1.0-1 and MQTT-4.8.0-1 of MQTT v3.1.1 while MQTT v3.1 is not that strict about this issue, but does also state &quot;When a TCP/IP socket connection is established from a client to a server, a protocol level session must be created using a CONNECT flow.&quot; (&lt;a href=&quot;http://public.dhe.ibm.com/software/dw/webservices/ws-mqtt/mqtt-v3r1.html#connect&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://public.dhe.ibm.com/software/dw/webservices/ws-mqtt/mqtt-v3r1.html#connect&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since ActiveMQ supports MQTT v3.1 according to &lt;a href=&quot;http://activemq.apache.org/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://activemq.apache.org/&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;br/&gt;
but also MQTT v3.1.1 according to Issue &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-4990&quot; title=&quot;Add support for the changes in MQTT 3.1.1&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AMQ-4990&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AMQ-4990&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I am not sure whether this should actually be considered a bug. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Ubuntu Linux 14.04 &lt;/p&gt;</environment>
